<p id="Par9" class="p">A change in global dust loading changes the dust DRE, which constitutes a radiative forcing. Since the dust DRE is approximately linear in the global dust loading
 <sup class="sup">
  <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR1" class="xref">1</xref>,
  <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR6" class="xref">6</xref>
 </sup>, the dust direct radiative forcing at TOA relative to the present-day climate, Δζ, can be approximated as:
 <disp-formula id="Equ3" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">3</label>
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M9" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$R_{{\mathrm{dust}}}\left( t \right) = {\mathrm{\Delta }}\zeta \left( t \right) \approx \zeta _0\frac{{L\left( t \right) - L_{\mathrm{0}}}}{{L_0}},$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M10" display="block" class="math">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">R</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">dust</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mfenced close=")" open="(" separators="" class="mfenced">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">t</mi>
     </mrow>
    </mfenced>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
    <mi class="mi">ζ</mi>
    <mfenced close=")" open="(" separators="" class="mfenced">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">t</mi>
     </mrow>
    </mfenced>
    <mo class="mo">≈</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">ζ</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mn class="mn">0</mn>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">L</mi>
      <mfenced close=")" open="(" separators="" class="mfenced">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">t</mi>
       </mrow>
      </mfenced>
      <mo class="mo">-</mo>
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">L</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">0</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">L</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mn class="mn">0</mn>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
    <mo class="mo">,</mo>
   </math>
   <graphic xlink:href="41467_2017_2620_Article_Equ3.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula>where 
 <italic class="italic">L</italic>(
 <italic class="italic">t</italic>) is the global dust loading at a future time 
 <italic class="italic">t</italic>, and 
 <italic class="italic">L</italic>
 <sub class="sub">0</sub> is the present-day dust loading. Furthermore, 
 <italic class="italic">ζ</italic>
 <sub class="sub">0</sub> is the dust DRE in the present-day climate, which was recently constrained to a median value of −0.20 Wm
 <sup class="sup">−2</sup> with a 95% confidence interval (CI) of −0.48 to +0.20 Wm
 <sup class="sup">[−2 
  <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR1" class="xref">1</xref>
 </sup>. Combining Eqs. (
 <xref rid="Equ2" ref-type="" class="xref">2</xref>) and (
 <xref rid="Equ3" ref-type="" class="xref">3</xref>) then yields the global direct dust–climate feedback as
 <disp-formula id="Equ4" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">4</label>
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M11" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\lambda _{{\mathrm{dust}}} \equiv \frac{{\partial R_{{\mathrm{dust}}}\left( t \right)}}{{\partial T\left( t \right)}} \cong \zeta _0\frac{{{\mathrm{\Delta }}L\left( t \right)/L_0}}{{{\mathrm{\Delta }}T\left( t \right)}} \equiv \zeta _0\kappa ,$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M12" display="block" class="math">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">λ</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">dust</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">≡</mo>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">∂</mi>
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">R</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">dust</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
      <mfenced close=")" open="(" separators="" class="mfenced">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">t</mi>
       </mrow>
      </mfenced>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">∂</mi>
      <mi class="mi">T</mi>
      <mfenced close=")" open="(" separators="" class="mfenced">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">t</mi>
       </mrow>
      </mfenced>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
    <mo class="mo">≅</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">ζ</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mn class="mn">0</mn>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
      <mi class="mi">L</mi>
      <mfenced close=")" open="(" separators="" class="mfenced">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">t</mi>
       </mrow>
      </mfenced>
      <mo class="mo">∕</mo>
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">L</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mn class="mn">0</mn>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
      <mi class="mi">T</mi>
      <mfenced close=")" open="(" separators="" class="mfenced">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">t</mi>
       </mrow>
      </mfenced>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
    <mo class="mo">≡</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">ζ</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mn class="mn">0</mn>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mi class="mi">κ</mi>
    <mo class="mo">,</mo>
   </math>
   <graphic xlink:href="41467_2017_2620_Article_Equ4.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula>where we defined 
 <inline-formula id="IEq3" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M13" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\kappa \equiv \frac{{{\mathrm{\Delta }}L/L_0}}{{{\mathrm{\Delta }}T}}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M14" class="math">
    <mi class="mi">κ</mi>
    <mo class="mo">≡</mo>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
      <mi class="mi">L</mi>
      <mo class="mo">∕</mo>
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">L</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mn class="mn">0</mn>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
      <mi class="mi">T</mi>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2017_2620_Article_IEq3.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> as the fractional change in the global dust loading per degree global surface temperature change.
</p>
